<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-120-189 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 057 853</DOCID><JOURNAL>Simulation  July 1991 v57 n1 p48(8).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A real-time simulator for the shuttle manipulator system in thesystem engineering laboratory. (space shuttle) (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Yang, Y.K.; Kuo, Y.M.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Space Shuttle's Shuttle Remote Manipulator System (SRMS)performs payload deployment and retrieval operations in additionto berthing tasks inside and near the shuttle's cargo bay.andP;  Thecomplex arm comprises seven rotational joints that function asshoulder, swing-out, shoulder yaw, shoulder pitch, elbow pitch,wrist pitch, wrist yaw and wrist roll.andP;  A real-time simulator forthe SRMS comprises a control station that provides mode selectionswitches and two had controllers for translational and rotationalcommands.andP;  The simulator also features a display and controlsystem that enables the crew to input and monitor data, and togenerate joint rate commands.andP;  Torque output is yielded by a jointservo model receiving data from the SRMS control system.andP;  Aflexible arm dynamic model gives dynamic responses of the arm tothe servo torques and other environmental torques.andP;  Finally, scenegenerators give visual displays for the crew using the SRMSpilot-in-the-loop simulator.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     SimulationSpace CraftResearch and DevelopmentRobot ArmsReal-Time Systems.andO;Feature:   illustrationchartphotograph.andO;Caption:   Requirements for a real-time Shuttle Remote Manipulator Systemsimulator. (chart)Software structure of the Shuttle Remote Manipulator Systemsystems. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>